	</div>
	<div align="center" class="main-content">
		<div class="spacer">
	</div><br>			<label class="collapse_ACT" for="_1"><font size="5px">HdfR transcriptional activity</font></label>
				<input id="_1" type="checkbox">
				<div class="ACT"><br><ul><li>Transcription from this promoter is regulated by numerous conditions and regulators , including DNA supercoiling , temperature , growth-phase , cell cycle , cyclic AMP receptor protein , OmpR , H-NS , HdfR , and LrhA ( 11 , 37 , 44 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=14645287" target="_blank">14645287</a>]<br></li>
<li>Although the nucleoid-associated protein H-NS is also required for optimal motility in Salmonella , our results indicate that it is not involved in the repression of flagella at low pH ; immunoblots showed that H-NS levels were unaffected by exposure of cells to low pH. This observation also suggests that the signal transduction system responsible for pH dependent regulation of flagellar genes , does not operate via the HdfR protein , a member of the LysR family that has recently been reported to-bind to the flhCD promoter of E. coli and that is controlled by H-NS levels [ 39 ] .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11681212" target="_blank">11681212</a>]<br></li>
<li>Altogether , these observations suggest that Dam meth-ylation and SeqA repress std operon expression and that HdfR activates std expression if either SeqA is absent or the genome lacks N6-methyl-adenosine .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=18805972" target="_blank">18805972</a>]<br></li>
<li>In S. enterica serotype Typhimurium , expression of fimbriae encoded by the std operon is under negative control by Dam methylase , SeqA , HdfR and the RosE repressor protein ( Jakomin et al. , 2008 , Chessa et al. , 2008b , Balbontin et al. , 2006 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19183274" target="_blank">19183274</a>]<br></li>
<li>Regulation of the Salmonella enterica std Fimbrial Operon Adenine Methylation , SeqA , and HdfR Marcello Jakomin ,1 Daniela Chessa ,2 Andreas J. Bäumler ,2 and Josep Casadesús1 * Departamento de Genética , Universidad de Sevilla , Apartado 1095 , Seville 41080 , Spain ,1 and Department of Medical Microbiology and Immunology , School of Medicine , University of California at Davis , One Shields Avenue , Davis , California 956126-86452 Received 13 August 2008/Accepted 30 August 2008 by DNA DNA adenine methylase ( dam ) mutants of Salmonella enterica serovar Typhimurium grown under laboratory conditions express the std ﬁmbrial operon , which is tightly repressed in the wild type .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=18805972" target="_blank">18805972</a>]<br></li>
<li>Jakomin , M. , D. Chessa , A. J. Baumler , and J. Casadesus , 2008 Regulation of the Salmonella enterica std ﬁmbrial operon by DNA adenine methylation , SeqA , and HdfR .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=25991823" target="_blank">25991823</a>]<br></li>
				</div></ul><br>
			<label class="collapse_EVO" for="_3"><font size="5px">HdfR evolution</font></label>
				<input id="_3" type="checkbox">
				<div class="EVO"><br><ul><li>Furthermore , we show that the GATC-binding protein SeqA is a repressor of the std operon and that the poorly known protein HdfR , a putative member of the LysR family of transcriptional regulators ( 29 ) , is an activator of std expression whose activity may be antagonized by SeqA .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=18805972" target="_blank">18805972</a>]<br></li>
<li>Because 82 % identity is found between the E. coli HdfR and Salmonella YifA ORFs ( data not shown ) , the serovar Typhimurium yifA gene was renamed hdfR .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=18805972" target="_blank">18805972</a>]<br></li>
				</div></ul><br>
			<label class="collapse_RP" for="_4"><font size="5px">Processes regulated by HdfR</font></label>
				<input id="_4" type="checkbox">
				<div class="RP"><br><ul><li>Gene , operon or Location Cellular function locus Phenotype affected Molecular mechanism Known regulators ﬂjBA , ﬂiC ﬁm gtr Chromosome Chromosome Motility , adhesion and virulence Adhesion to the intestinal epithelium Lipopolysaccharide O-antigen glycosylation Modiﬁcation of O-antigen chain length Adhesion to the intestinal epithelium Adhesion to the intestinal epithelium Epithelial cell invasion Bioﬁlm formation Motility , adhesion and virulence Flagella Fimbriae LPS Site-speciﬁc recombination Unknown DNA-methylation pattern Hin FimB , FimE OxyR Chromosome and prophage P22 Chromosome Virulence plasmid Chromosome Chromosome Chromosome Chromosome Chromosome Chromosome opvAB pef std SPI-1 csgD ﬂiC lpf iol LPS Fimbriae DNA-methylation pattern DNA-methylation pattern DNA-methylation pattern Unknown Unknown Unknown Unknown Unknown OxyR Lrp , PefI Fimbriae TTSS Extracellular matrix Flagella Fimbriae myo-inositol utilization Dam , HdfR , RosE , SeqA StdE , StdF , FliZ c-di-GMP FliA , ClpX , FliZ , YdiV IolR , ReiD Fig. 1 .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=29369799" target="_blank">29369799</a>]<br></li>
<li>Transcription from this promoter is regulated by numerous conditions and regulators , including DNA supercoiling , temperature , growth phase , cell-cycle , cyclic AMP receptor protein , OmpR , H-NS , HdfR , and LrhA ( 11 , 37 , 44 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=14645287" target="_blank">14645287</a>]<br></li>
<li>This second screen identiﬁed HdfR ( previously , YifA ) as a function needed for std expression in dam and seqA mutants .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=18805972" target="_blank">18805972</a>]<br></li>
<li>In S. enterica serotype Typhimurium , expression of fimbriae encoded by the std operon is under negative control by Dam methylase , SeqA , HdfR and the RosE repressor protein ( Jakomin et al. , 2008 , Chessa et al. , 2008b , Balbontin et al. , 2006 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19183274" target="_blank">19183274</a>]<br></li>
<li>In addition , DsrA may fall into Group I sRNAs , as it directly stimulates translation of rpoS mRNA , whereas it interferes with the expression of H-NS , which -- by repressing the expression of the flhDC repressor HdfR -- acts as an indirect activator of FlhDC expression .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=23443158" target="_blank">23443158</a>]<br></li>
<li>Other regulators implicated in control of ﬂhDC include catabolite gene activator protein ( 48 , 74 ) , LrhA ( 51 ) and HNS , via HdfR ( 47 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12923082" target="_blank">12923082</a>]<br></li>
<li>Previous reports claimed that H-NS plays an indirect role in the ﬂhDC operon involved in ﬂagellation synthesis via HdfR ( 1 , 23 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=18156266" target="_blank">18156266</a>]<br></li>
				</div></ul><br>
			<label class="collapse_SIT" for="_5"><font size="5px">HdfR binding site</font></label>
				<input id="_5" type="checkbox">
				<div class="SIT"><br><ul><li>Unpublished results from our group suggest that HdfR binds the std promoter in a Dam methylation-dependent manner , thereby blocking methylation of 2 GATC sites at the std upstream regulatory region .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=29369799" target="_blank">29369799</a>]<br></li>
				</ul></div><br>
			<label class="collapse_TU" for="_6"><font size="5px">Transcription unit regulated by HdfR</font></label>
				<input id="_6" type="checkbox">
				<div class="TU"><br><ul><li>Activation of std expression by HdfR is observed only in dam and seqA backgrounds .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=18805972" target="_blank">18805972</a>]<br></li>
<li>Lack of HdfR does not alter std expression in a seqA dam background ( data not shown ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=18805972" target="_blank">18805972</a>]<br></li>
<li>Altogether , these observations suggest that Dam meth-ylation and SeqA repress std operon expression and that HdfR activates std expression if either SeqA is absent or the genome lacks N6-methyl-adenosine .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=18805972" target="_blank">18805972</a>]<br></li>
<li>In S. enterica serotype Typhimurium , expression of fimbriae encoded by the std operon is under negative control by Dam methylase , SeqA , HdfR and the RosE repressor protein ( Jakomin et al. , 2008 , Chessa et al. , 2008b , Balbontin et al. , 2006 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19183274" target="_blank">19183274</a>]<br></li>
